STAY AWAY FROM HERE..terrible experience..will not be coming here..unless they get they act together... I will be reporting them to the better business administration..to file a complaint on there ridiculous pricing...

The best jerk chicken EVER. I took a chance on this place, it was small but super clean, every dish (fish, bbq ribs, curry and stew) looked fresh and appetizing. I ordered a large and it was indeed large like I wanted. The chicken was grilled and absolutely delicious. Actual half chicken pieces. The collared greens and mac and cheese was fresh and good also. I loved the side of jerk sauce, and the chunky savory oxtail gravy the lady already knew to put on the rice. I didn't have to haggle for more in the plate, the large was worth the 13 bucks. I WILL BE COMING BACK THERE!!! The server was nice. The place is wheelchair accessible.  The only thing is they are CASH ONLY. ATM on the premises.

Terrible Terrible Terrible "customer service"Now this is actually the second time that I called this restaurant. First time was only because they are the only Jamaican spot near by and second was just now to place an order. The lady answering the phone sounds miserable!!!! She hangs up the phone after I questioned the delivery process. I guess she was clueless so she hung up but to make matters worse when I called back & asked to speak with a manager she hangs up again & forwards my calls SO n/a. I've been to this disgusting place twice.  The first time, I  placed an order for oxtails, peas and rice, and collard greens because the cabbage was gone. The oxtails were decent, but I've still had better. My problem here, is that the food was cold, and the collard greens were from the bottom of the pot. They were extremely salty, and black bits in them. I decided to try it again, after getting off of work late one night. I ordered curried  chicken and rice. The same thing again! Cold food.  I had to warm it uo, which I regret because my stomach killed me the entire night. Beware people. I won't be back. Honestly the worse carribean place I've ever been to, especially being in New York

If I could rate a zero, I would. I called for a delivery and the female who answered the phone was rude and had me on hold for 8 minutes while having a conversation with her coworkers in the background about other customers. She used profanity and made fun of people and spoke of "spitting in food". She obviously forgot that I was holding on the line. I hung up and called back for an explanation and she hung up in my face. I called again because just maybe I'm not heard. She answers with a nasty tone and I ask again as to why I was on hold, why was she cursing and mainly WHY are you speaking of spitting in food??!! Her response, "if you're not going to order, you shouldn't be calling" and hangs up in my face AGAIN......I WILL NEVER eat from them and I am going to make it my business to reach the owner. Hopefully it's not a family member or one of the other rude and unprofessional employees that was screaming in the background telling her to hang up the phone in my face. DON'T EAT FROM THIS PLACE.
